ltl3ba
------------------------------------------
LTL3BA is a translator of LTL formulae to Büchi automata. It is based on the
popular tool named LTL2BA written by Denis Oddoux and Paul Gastin.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.10-1
  libbdd0-2.4-1bl6
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  libbdd-devel-2.4-1bl6
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/ltl3ba/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/ltl3ba/ltl3ba-1.1.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ltl3ba-1.1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ltl3ba-1.1.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ltl3ba-1.1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ltl3ba-1.1.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ltl3ba)
  /usr/bin/ltl3ba.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ltl3ba.README
  /usr/share/doc/ltl3ba/Changelog
  /usr/share/doc/ltl3ba/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/ltl3ba/README

------------------

